It has a plain olive back running from its forehead down to its uppertail coverts, and an yellow underside from its throat to its nape, belly and underside coverts. It has a black curved bill and black legs.

description:
It is a very small bird with a thin and long beak relative to its size. The beak seemed somewhere in between something adapted to nectar feeling and generalist type of beak. It has a dark head with the colouration extending till its breast (possibly seen that way due to the lighting conditions at that time) lower parts are bright yellow. 

It was seen flying rapidly tree to tree. Some other individuals of the same species were also seen picking up tiny twigs and possibly transporting them to their nest.

Yellow belly. Shiny purplish blue throat. Olive colored wings and back. White under tail coverts. Black beak. Male.

Spotted at landed residential estates.
